Interface CallableSBase

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, NamedSBase, NamedSBaseWithDerivedUnit, SBase, SBaseWithDerivedUnit, java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Quantity, Variable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Compartment, Dimension, FunctionDefinition, Input, IntraSpeciesReaction, LocalParameter, Output, Parameter, QuantityWithUnit, Reaction, Species, SpeciesReference, Symbol

    public interface CallableSBase
extends NamedSBaseWithDerivedUnit
    The interface CallableSBase represents an SBase that can be called in mathematical expressions, i.e., ASTNode, via its identifier. In terms of serialized SBML files, the identifiers of instances of CallableSBase can be used in ci elements within MathML expressions. All these elements can be found in the specification of SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core, Table 1 on page 21. Furthermore, LocalParameter also belongs to these elements.
    Since:
    0.8
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger
